This paper deals with ontology approximation, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several subfields of computer science. The paper discusses approximation of ontologies formulated in a non-Horn description logic, which is a topic that is closely related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and logic (cs.LO). The paper also discusses ontology-mediated querying, which is a topic that is related to databases (cs.DB) and natural language processing (cs.CL). Finally, the paper discusses subsumption-based approximations, which is a topic that is related to cryptography (cs.CR). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories for this paper are cs.AI, cs.LO, cs.DB, cs.CL, and cs.CR, in that order.
